The paper deals with the complexity of distributional problems and their algorithms, which are typically studied in the computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The use of probability and juntas also suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the study of self-knowingly correct algorithms relates to the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
